{"name": "pyesoify", "metadata": {"name": "pyesoify", "version": "0.1", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "home_page": "https://github.com/tathyagarg/pyeosify", "license": "MIT", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "A simple Python package to convert Python code to a much, much, much less readable form.", "upload_time": 1734723526}, "documentation": [""], "modules": [{"name": "pyesoify.functions.chr", "documentation": ["chr.py\n~~~~~~\n\nThis module contains the chr function.\n`chr` can be accessed through `__builtins__.__getitem__(\"chr\")`.\n\nSo, our task is really to obfuscate `\"chr\"` in the code.\n`__builtins__` contains all the built-in functions.\n\nWe can get the chr function through:\n`__builtins__[\"chr\"]`, but this requires `\"chr\"` and that's annoying.\nSo, we get an iterator, convert to list, index to get `chr`\n\n`__builtins__.__iter__()`\n=> `[*__builtins__.__iter__()]`\n\nElement at index 14 is `chr`, so we can get `chr` through:\n`[*__builtins__.__iter__()][14]`\n\nSo, we only require `14` in the code."], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "pyesoify.functions.chr.CHR", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "pyesoify.string_factory", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "pyesoify.string_factory.make_string", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "text", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "pyesoify.functions.map", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "pyesoify.functions.map.MAP", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "pyesoify.functions.getattr", "documentation": ["getattr.py\n~~~~~~~~~~\n\nThis module contains the getattribute function.\n`getattribute` can be accessed through `__builtins__.__getitem__(\"getattr\")`."], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "pyesoify.functions.getattr.GETATTR", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "pyesoify.functions.print", "documentation": ["print.py\n~~~~~~~~\n\nThis module contains the print function.\n`print` can be accessed through `__builtins__.__getattribute__(\"print\")`.\nSo, our task is really to obfuscate `\"print\"` in the code.\n\nWe'll do this by obfuscating `''.join(\"print\")`\nWhich is `str().join(\"print\")`\n=> `str().join([\"p\", \"r\", \"i\", \"n\", \"t\"])`\n=> `str().join([chr(112), chr(114), chr(105), chr(110), chr(116)])`\n=> `str().join(map(chr, [112, 114, 105, 110, 116]))`\n=> `str().join(map(chr, [0x70, 0x72, 0x69, 0x6e, 0x74]))`"], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "pyesoify.functions.print.PRINT", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "pyesoify.functions._str", "documentation": ["str.py\n~~~~~~\n\nThis module contains the str function.\n`str` can be accessed through `__builtins__.__getitem__(\"str\")`.\nSo, our task is really to obfuscate `\"str\"` in the code.\n\nTo avoid a \"recursive obfuscation\"(?) of `str`, we will not use the `str` function to obfuscate `str`.\nSince `str` is just 3 letters, and I can't use `str` already, we'll manually `+` the characters.\nThus, we need `'s' + 't' + 'r'`\n\n=> `'s' + 't' + 'r'`\n=> `chr(115) + chr(116) + chr(114)`\n=> `chr(0x73) + chr(0x74) + chr(0x72)`\n=> `chr(0x73).__add__(chr(0x74)).__add__(chr(0x72))`\n\nLet a = 0x73 (115)\n\n=> `chr(a).__add__(chr(a + 1)).__add__(chr(a - 1))`\n=> `chr(a).__add__(chr(a.__add__(1))).__add__(chr(a.__sub__(1)))`\n\nThus, we require `chr`, `a` (115), `1` in this code."], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "pyesoify.functions._str.STR", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "pyesoify.numbers", "documentation": ["numbers.py\n~~~~~~~~~~\n\nThis module contains the numbers used in the code.\nThe first ten numbers are defined through the equivalent of the following lambda calculus expressions:\n\nTWO = lambda f: lambda x: f(f(x))\nTHREE = lambda f: lambda x: f(f(f(x)))\n...\n\nWhere `f` is the increment function, and x is 1.\nThe increment function is defined as:\nINCREMENT = lambda x: x.__add__(1)\n\nThis is impractical to do for larger numbers. So numbers post 10 will be defined uniquely."], "functions": [{"name": "pyesoify.numbers.obfs_number", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "n", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}], "variables": [{"name": "pyesoify.numbers.ONE", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyesoify.numbers.INCREMENT", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyesoify.numbers.TWO", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyesoify.numbers.THREE", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyesoify.numbers.FOUR", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyesoify.numbers.FIVE", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyesoify.numbers.SIX", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyesoify.numbers.SEVEN", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyesoify.numbers.EIGHT", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyesoify.numbers.NINE", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyesoify.numbers.TEN", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyesoify.numbers.ELEVEN", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyesoify.numbers.TWELVE", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyesoify.numbers.THIRTEEN", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyesoify.numbers.OFFSETS", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyesoify.numbers.FOURTEEN", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyesoify.numbers.FIFTEEN", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyesoify.numbers.STRONG", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyesoify.numbers.HUNDERED", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyesoify.numbers.HUNDERED_FIFTEEN", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyesoify.numbers.HUNDERED_TEN", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyesoify.numbers.SEVENTY", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyesoify.numbers.SEVENTY_EIGHT", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "pyesoify", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "pyesoify.pyesoify", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "pyesoify.pyesoify.get_code", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "fpath", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyesoify.pyesoify.main", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "code", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "pyesoify.operators", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "pyesoify.operators.obfs_operator", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "op", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "pyesoify.functions", "documentation": ["I've used __builtins__ extensively without obfuscation. This is because the obfuscation of __builtins__ is not necessary (it's tricky, too)."], "functions":